   "source": [
    "# Every Matplotlib Plot Linestyle\n",
    "\n",
    "<span>Matplotlib has many lifestyles for its line plots. Sometimes is hard to visualize each lifestyle from just its line marker. Therefore I created a quick notebook to plot each line style out. I often come back to these plot to refresh my memory.</span>\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "linestyle documentation:  https://matplotlib.org/devdocs/gallery/lines_bars_and_markers/line_styles_reference.html \n",
    "\n",
    "### Import Preliminaries"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "metadata": {
    "ExecuteTime": {
     "end_time": "2018-09-11T00:29:42.910275Z",
     "start_time": "2018-09-11T00:29:42.532867Z"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "%matplotlib inline\n",
    "%config InlineBackend.figure_format='retina'\n",
    "\n",
    "# Import modules\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "\n",
    "# A list of all linestyles\n",
    "linestyles = ['-','--','-.',':']"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "ExecuteTime": {
     "end_time": "2018-07-06T12:38:43.903985Z",
     "start_time": "2018-07-06T12:38:43.898481Z"
    }
   },
   "source": [
    "### Visualize Matplotlib Markers"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "metadata": {

   "source": [
    "# Plot a line for every linestyle in our list\n",
    "for line in linestyles:\n",
    "    data = pd.DataFrame(np.random.choice([1,2,3,4], replace=True, size=10), \n",
    "                      columns=['Col A'])\n",
    "    plt.plot(data.index,data['Col A'], linestyle=line, \n",
    "           color='purple', linewidth=3)\n",
    "    plt.title('\"'+str(line)+'\" '+'Line Style')\n",
    "    plt.ylabel('Y Label')\n",
    "    plt.xlabel('X Label')\n",
    "    plt.show()"
   ]
  },
